FBIS4-2878 "drchi072_k_94001" FBIS-CHI-94-072 Daily Report 13 Apr 1994 NATIONAL AFFAIRS Political & Social Communications Ministry Issues Circular on Boating Safety Communications Ministry Issues Circular on Boating Safety OW1404010194 Beijing Central People's Radio Network in Mandarin 1030 GMT 13 Apr 94 OW1404010194 Beijing Central People's Radio Network Mandarin BFN [From the "National Hookup" program] [Text] The Ministry of Communications recently issued an emergency circular on strengthening control over safety during springtime. The circular bans lake or river cruises during springtime by boats and ships without a certificate of registry or an operating license. Units that solicit tourists and use boats, as well as boatmen and shipowners shall be held responsible if an accident occurs due to their failure to comply with this requirement. Boats and ships that take passengers on a spring cruise must strictly comply with the regulations on the maximum capacity of passengers permitted on board, and must be equipped with standard lifesaving appliances as well as standard fire fighting facilities. The circular requires departments responsible for transportation, and harbor navigation superintendency administrations at all levels to conduct widespread propaganda of the laws and regulations on surface transportation safety. As regards boats and ships that take passengers on spring cruises in violation of regulations, harbor navigation superintendency administrations are required to sternly punish boatmen, shipowners, and the crew responsible for such violations according to the law.
